article.description: Alabama A&M uses 3's to top Jackson St, 68-61
article.headline: Alabama A&M uses 3's to top Jackson St, 68-61
article.linkText: Alabama A&M uses 3's to top Jackson St, 68-61
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. -- Jeremy Crutcher scored 16 points as Alabama A&M used 3-point shooting to post a 68-61 win over Jackson State in the Southwestern Conference opener for both schools Saturday night. Neither team shot the ball well. Alabama A&M was 18 of 46 from the field; Jackson State 18 of 42. The Bulldogs, however, converted 8 of 23 from behind the arc. Green Hill scored 14 points for Alabama A&M (4-7, 1-0 SWAC). Jerome Hunter added 10 points and eight boards. Brandon West scored 19 points and Jeffery Stubbs added another 14 for Jackson State (4-9) in first-year coach Wayne Brent's SWAC debut. Derell Taylor, the lone returning starter from a year ago, added 12 points and Treshawn Bolden contributed 10. The Tigers leading scorer Julysses Nobles, who averages more than 17 points per game, was 0-for-3 from the field with five turnovers and did not play in the second half.
